race.comment: DUBAI AFFAIR (9) resumes for the Trinder yard with a top hoop booked. She placed heavily bet her last four and her trials have been sharp. Looks on song and this is winnable. VERHOEVEN (5) was quickly back on track missing a whisker here this trip. Settled last off the outside barrier, and it was an impressive effort. Will have to do it the hard way again but is well placed with the 3kg claim. GEEGEES MERCEDES (11) disappointed here last time but he'd been going well prior. Presents on a 7-day return with the winkers on for the first time and finally draws a decent gate. LIGHT WORK (13) Was heavily bet here on debut and didn't get into it. Resumes from a low barrier with a 3kg claim and has been fitted with two trials. Worth a betting watch.
